    Cable stayed bridge across river Han
    This is a Cable stayed bridge across river Han. It comes to life during night time. It is located near the International Airport. If one takes a river cruise during night time one can enjoy the beauty of the same.
    Visited August 2023
    Traveled with family
    Written August 24, 2023
  • Lester Gencianeo
    Macau, China731 contributions
    Da Nang at night
    Went for an evening cruise with family. Da Nang is beautiful at night. It was a good experience as it's not crowded with tourists during our trip. There are different ferry operators on the dock, the one we chose provided us with a cup of fruits and a bottled water, on-board ordering for snacks is also available. There is short traditional dance performance at the start of the cruise.
    Visited May 2023
    Traveled with family
    Written December 30, 2023
  • Wonder A
    417 contributions
    The Vibrant Han River
    A symbol of Danang City, the Han River Bridge was the first swing bridge in Vietnam, symbolizing new vitality and developing desire of the city. Along the Han River were two beautiful water-front streets. Visitors and locals flocked the area for its night-life activities such as pub, bar and street-dancing.
    Visited February 2024
    Traveled as a couple
    Written April 6, 2024
  • LolaGo1
    Washington DC, District of Columbia6,628 contributions
    It is just a bridge!
    I passed this bridge while walking back from the Danang Museum to my hotel around noon. Except for the cars and other transports crossing it, there was nothing else to see here. The Dragon Bridge is much better, has more things near it to see, eat, watch, etc. Perhaps in the evening when it gets dark and cooler, it would be a better experience!
    Visited April 2024
    Traveled solo
    Written April 14, 2024
